spec: abc_extra58
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(abc)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/abc.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/abc.html — Python abc module documentation"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/reference/datamodel.html#inspect — Python function __defaults__, __code__, and __closure__ documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/abc.py"
    - "CPython source: Modules/_abc.c"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends abc_extra57.zspec.zsdl."
    - "Prior specs covered: ABC/__name__/__module__/__qualname__/__bases__[0].__name__, ABCMeta/__name__/__module__/__qualname__, abstractmethod/__name__/__module__/__qualname__, get_cache_token/__name__/__module__/__qualname__, __module__/__name__/__qualname__.__len__() for all abc exports, abstractproperty/abstractclassmethod/abstractstaticmethod lengths/qualnames/bases, ABCMeta.register qualname lengths/equality, ABCMeta method __qualname__.__len__() tables, __mro__.__len__() for ABCMeta(3)/ABC(2)/abstractproperty(3)/abstractclassmethod(3)/abstractstaticmethod(3), __bases__[0].__name__.__len__(), __dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__() tables, ABCMeta/__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') (extra9), ABC/__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') (extra8), ABCMeta/__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ and ABC/__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ (extra49), abstractproperty/abstractclassmethod/abstractstaticmethod __dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') (extra49), abc module __dict__.__class__.__name__/__qualname__ (extra49), abstractmethod/__class__.__name__=='function', abstractproperty/__class__.__name__=='type', ABC/__class__.__name__=='ABCMeta' (extra40), __class__.__qualname__ string equality for all abc exports (extra41-extra43), abstractmethod/__class__.__module__=='builtins', abstractproperty/__class__.__module__=='builtins', ABC/__class__.__module__=='abc', ABCMeta/__class__.__module__=='builtins', abstractclassmethod/__class__.__module__=='builtins', abstractstaticmethod/__class__.__module__=='builtins' (extra42), abstractproperty/__init__.__class__.__name__=='wrapper_descriptor', abstractmethod/__init__.__class__.__name__=='method-wrapper' (extra50), __class__.__module__.__len__() cross-checks (extra50), __repr__.__class__.__name__ for all abc objects (extra51), __weakref__.__class__.__name__ for abstractproperty/abstractclassmethod/abstractstaticmethod (extra51), ABCMeta.__instancecheck__/__subclasscheck__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function') (extra52), ABC/ABCMeta __eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor') (extra52), abc.__package__.__eq__('') (extra53), ABC/ABCMeta/abstractmethod/get_cache_token __doc__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('str') (extra53), ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__qualname__.__eq__('ABCMeta.__instancecheck__') (extra53), __loader__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('type') (extra54), __loader__.__name__.__eq__('FrozenImporter') (extra54), __spec__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('ModuleSpec') (extra54), __file__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('str') (extra54), ABCMeta.__instancecheck__.__qualname__.__len__()==25 (extra54), __spec__.origin/__spec__.submodule_search_locations/__spec__.has_location/__loader__.__name__.__len__() (extra55), ABCMeta.register/__instancecheck__/__subclasscheck__/update_abstractmethods __qualname__.__eq__ (extra56), abstractproperty.__init__.__qualname__.__eq__('property.__init__') (extra56), abstractmethod/__annotations__/__globals__ class identity, ABCMeta/__doc__.__contains__('Abstract'), get_cache_token.__class__.__name__.__eq__('builtin_function_or_method') (extra57)."
    - "This spec covers (abccode58 namespace): wave 229 theme — __defaults__ and __code__ checks for function parameters + __closure__ identity. NEW in extra58: abstractmethod.__defaults__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('NoneType') — abstractmethod(funcobj) has no default arguments; __defaults__ is None; None.__class__.__name__ is 'NoneType'; no prior abc spec has checked abstractmethod.__defaults__.__class__.__name__ via __eq__; abstractmethod.__code__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('code') — abstractmethod is a pure-Python function with a code object; __class__.__name__ is 'code'; no prior abc spec has checked abstractmethod.__code__.__class__.__name__ via __eq__; abstractmethod.__closure__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('NoneType') — abstractmethod is a module-level function with no free variables; __closure__ is None; None.__class__.__name__ is 'NoneType'; no prior abc spec has checked abstractmethod.__closure__.__class__.__name__ via __eq__; update_abstractmethods.__defaults__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('NoneType') and update_abstractmethods.__code__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('code') — update_abstractmethods(cls) has no default arguments and is a pure-Python function."
    - "abc.abstractmethod.__defaults__ is None. abstractmethod(funcobj) takes one positional-or-keyword parameter (funcobj) with no default. __defaults__ is None. None.__class__.__name__ is 'NoneType'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.abstractmethod.__code__.__class__.__name__ == 'code'. abstractmethod is a pure-Python function defined in Lib/abc.py. All pure-Python functions have a __code__ attribute that is a code object. __class__.__name__ of a code object is 'code'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.abstractmethod.__closure__ is None. abstractmethod is defined at module level in Lib/abc.py and does not capture any free variables from an enclosing scope. Functions with no free variables have __closure__ == None. None.__class__.__name__ is 'NoneType'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.update_abstractmethods.__defaults__ is None. update_abstractmethods(cls) takes one positional-or-keyword parameter (cls) with no default. __defaults__ is None. None.__class__.__name__ is 'NoneType'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "abc.update_abstractmethods.__code__.__class__.__name__ == 'code'. update_abstractmethods is a pure-Python function defined in Lib/abc.py. Its __code__ attribute is a code object with __class__.__name__ == 'code'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# abc abstractmethod __defaults__, __code__, and __closure__ checks — extra58
#
# Wave 229 theme: __defaults__ and __code__ checks + __closure__ identity.
#
# abstractmethod(funcobj) has no default arguments, so __defaults__ is None.
# abstractmethod is a pure-Python function with a code object (__code__).
# abstractmethod is a module-level function with no free variables, so
# __closure__ is None (NoneType).
#
# NEW: no prior abc spec has checked __defaults__.__class__.__name__,
# __code__.__class__.__name__, or __closure__.__class__.__name__ via __eq__
# for abstractmethod.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table abc_extra58.abstractmethod_defaults_code_closure:
  description: "abc abstractmethod __defaults__/__code__/__closure__ __class__.__name__.__eq__ checks in abccode58 namespace — wave 229 theme: __defaults__ and __code__ checks + __closure__ identity; abstractmethod(funcobj) has no default arguments (__defaults__ is None, NoneType); abstractmethod is a pure-Python function (__code__.__class__.__name__ == 'code'); abstractmethod is a non-closure function (__closure__ is None, NoneType); NEW in extra58: no prior abc spec has checked __defaults__/__code__/__closure__.__class__.__name__ via __eq__ for abstractmethod; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: defaults
  id_prefix: abccode58

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [abstractmethod_defaults_class, abstractmethod.__defaults__.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["NoneType"], true, "abstractmethod.__defaults__.__class__.__name__ == 'NoneType' — abstractmethod(funcobj) takes one positional-or-keyword parameter (funcobj) with no default; __defaults__ is None; None.__class__.__name__ is 'NoneType'; NEW in extra58: first __defaults__.__class__.__name__.__eq__ check for abstractmethod in any abc spec; verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [abstractmethod_code_class,     abstractmethod.__code__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,     ["code"],     true, "abstractmethod.__code__.__class__.__name__ == 'code' — abstractmethod is a pure-Python function defined in Lib/abc.py; all pure-Python functions have a __code__ attribute that is a code object; the type of a code object is <class 'code'>, so __class__.__name__ is 'code'; NEW in extra58: first __code__.__class__.__name__.__eq__ check for abstractmethod in any abc spec; verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [abstractmethod_closure_class,  abstractmethod.__closure__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,  ["NoneType"], true, "abstractmethod.__closure__.__class__.__name__ == 'NoneType' — abstractmethod is a module-level function in Lib/abc.py with no free variables from any enclosing scope; functions with no free variables have __closure__ == None; None.__class__.__name__ is 'NoneType'; NEW in extra58: first __closure__.__class__.__name__.__eq__ check for abstractmethod in any abc spec; verified with Python 3.14.3"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# abc update_abstractmethods __defaults__ and __code__ checks — extra58
#
# Wave 229 theme: __defaults__ and __code__ checks for function parameters.
#
# update_abstractmethods(cls) has no default arguments, so __defaults__ is None.
# update_abstractmethods is a pure-Python function with a code object.
#
# NEW: no prior abc spec has checked __defaults__.__class__.__name__ or
# __code__.__class__.__name__ via __eq__ for update_abstractmethods.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table abc_extra58.update_abstractmethods_defaults_and_code:
  description: "abc update_abstractmethods __defaults__/__code__ __class__.__name__.__eq__ checks in abccode58 namespace — wave 229 theme: __defaults__ and __code__ checks; update_abstractmethods(cls) has no default arguments (__defaults__ is None, NoneType); update_abstractmethods is a pure-Python function (__code__.__class__.__name__ == 'code'); NEW in extra58: no prior abc spec has checked __defaults__.__class__.__name__ or __code__.__class__.__name__ via __eq__ for update_abstractmethods; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: defaults
  id_prefix: abccode58u

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [uam_defaults_class, update_abstractmethods.__defaults__.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["NoneType"], true, "update_abstractmethods.__defaults__.__class__.__name__ == 'NoneType' — update_abstractmethods(cls) takes one positional-or-keyword parameter (cls) with no default; __defaults__ is None; None.__class__.__name__ is 'NoneType'; NEW in extra58: first __defaults__.__class__.__name__.__eq__ check for update_abstractmethods in any abc spec; verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [uam_code_class,     update_abstractmethods.__code__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,     ["code"],     true, "update_abstractmethods.__code__.__class__.__name__ == 'code' — update_abstractmethods is a pure-Python function defined in Lib/abc.py; its __code__ attribute is a code object with __class__.__name__ == 'code'; NEW in extra58: first __code__.__class__.__name__.__eq__ check for update_abstractmethods in any abc spec; verified with Python 3.14.3"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Standalone invariants — extra58
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant abc_extra58.abstractmethod_defaults_class_name_eq:
  description: "abc.abstractmethod.__defaults__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('NoneType') returns True — abstractmethod(funcobj) takes one positional-or-keyword parameter (funcobj) with no default; __defaults__ is None; None.__class__.__name__ is 'NoneType'; NEW in extra58: no prior abc spec has checked abstractmethod.__defaults__.__class__.__name__ via __eq__; wave 229 first __defaults__ class identity invariant for abstractmethod in any abc spec; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  category: defaults
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: abstractmethod.__defaults__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["NoneType"]
  expected: true

invariant abc_extra58.abstractmethod_code_class_name_eq:
  description: "abc.abstractmethod.__code__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('code') returns True — abstractmethod is a pure-Python function defined in Lib/abc.py; all pure-Python functions have a __code__ attribute that is a code object; the type of a code object is <class 'code'>, so __class__.__name__ is 'code'; NEW in extra58: no prior abc spec has checked abstractmethod.__code__.__class__.__name__ via __eq__; wave 229 first __code__ class identity invariant for abstractmethod in any abc spec; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  category: code
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: abstractmethod.__code__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["code"]
  expected: true

invariant abc_extra58.abstractmethod_closure_class_name_eq:
  description: "abc.abstractmethod.__closure__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('NoneType') returns True — abstractmethod is a module-level function in Lib/abc.py with no free variables from any enclosing scope; functions with no free variables have __closure__ == None; None.__class__.__name__ is 'NoneType'; NEW in extra58: no prior abc spec has checked abstractmethod.__closure__.__class__.__name__ via __eq__; wave 229 first __closure__ class identity invariant for abstractmethod in any abc spec; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  category: closure
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: abstractmethod.__closure__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["NoneType"]
  expected: true

invariant abc_extra58.update_abstractmethods_defaults_class_name_eq:
  description: "abc.update_abstractmethods.__defaults__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('NoneType') returns True — update_abstractmethods(cls) takes one positional-or-keyword parameter (cls) with no default; __defaults__ is None; None.__class__.__name__ is 'NoneType'; NEW in extra58: no prior abc spec has checked update_abstractmethods.__defaults__.__class__.__name__ via __eq__; wave 229 first __defaults__ class identity invariant for update_abstractmethods in any abc spec; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  category: defaults
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: update_abstractmethods.__defaults__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["NoneType"]
  expected: true

invariant abc_extra58.update_abstractmethods_code_class_name_eq:
  description: "abc.update_abstractmethods.__code__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('code') returns True — update_abstractmethods is a pure-Python function defined in Lib/abc.py; its __code__ attribute is a code object with __class__.__name__ == 'code'; NEW in extra58: no prior abc spec has checked update_abstractmethods.__code__.__class__.__name__ via __eq__; wave 229 invariant alongside abstractmethod code check; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  category: code
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: update_abstractmethods.__code__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["code"]
  expected: true
